  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nThe text alignment and the baseline of the implementation screen (on the right), is way lower than design on iOS:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"500\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-16 alle 09 38 17\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/122543089/190e60d9-f2ed-4075-90a5-18ef2f3c2638\">\r\n\r\nbut paddings, height, etc are correct.\r\n\r\nSo this is a problem related to the way iOS is adding spaces.\r\n\r\nMore context in these PR comments:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/17536#issuecomment-1762181874\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nText's paddings are distributed in the same way for both top and bottom.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nthe paddings of the iOS input are bigger in the top side when the input has more than one line.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Quo2 Preview -> inputs -> Input -> set `multiline?` as `true`\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n",
